subject: pcie_bifurcation: Fetch highest level bifurcation at a PCIe slot
commitMessage:
pcie_bifurcation: Fetch highest level bifurcation at a PCIe slot

Use the MaxLanes property defined in PCIeDevice and Lanes property
defined in PCIeSlot to construct the bifurication info.

The command will parse the i2c tree until it hit the PCIe device and
return the lanes that it uses. At each PCIe slots, it will try to find
the devices connected to it. All of the PCIe Devices/Slots needs to be
avaliable in FruDevice for this to work.

Tested:
Unit tests passed.

Physical Tests.

PE0 -> no bifurcation
PE1 -> x8x8

```
$ ipmitool raw 0x2e 0x32 0x79 0x2b 0x00 0x0f 0
 79 2b 00 0b 00

$ ipmitool raw 0x2e 0x32 0x79 0x2b 0x00 0x0f 1
 79 2b 00 0b 02 08 08
```

Change-Id: Id811897cad82a36da29cd8795f8bc6e855a7e96d
Signed-off-by: Willy Tu <wltu@google.com>
